# Project Conventions

- Target **UDM OS 4.3+** only. No compatibility with other *nix versions.
- Use only tools and commands available on UDM OS unless easily addable without affecting UDM stability.
- Do not assume backwards compatibility; single deployment. Reinstall on UDMs if needed. Ask before ignoring backwards compatibility.
- When multiple equally valid implementation paths exist, ask clarifying questions (for significant choices, not every detail).
- If a change does not fix the problem, revert it unless otherwise worthwhile. Minimize code churn when fixing bugs; add suggestions to FUTURE.md.
- When git commit hooks or associated scripts are updated, run `./scripts/setup-git-hooks.sh` so git uses them.
- **DO NOT FIT CODE TO TESTS.** Tests run the code. Fix bugs in code; do not change code only to satisfy tests.
